Series IV, the F. W. (Francis Woolsey) Bronson gift consists of material relating to Bronson's research into Robert Louis Stevenson's ballad the "Dead Man's Chest" (found in 
                     Treasure Island
                  ). The research files preserve Bronson's arrangement of numerically ordered groups of material relating to works, and include correspondence, clippings, printed works, and notes. Correspondence includes letters to Bronson from Young Ewing Allison, Ernest McNeill Eller, Lord Frederic Hamilton, John Ernest Levo, Michael Monahan, Vincent Starrett, Burton Egbert Stevenson, and others, as well as bookdealers, editors, and publishers.
